	   <tr><td colspan=2>You can get much better offhand weapons than the burning rapier for 560pp these days: absolutely true. Keep in mind the burning rapier came waay back with the original EQ. They've already upgraded it once (used to be like 7/24 w/ a 17dd proc) and that caused enough trouble and grief for them. They're probably way too concerned with adding in great new piercers right now than upgrading the old ones. Does all that mean you shouldn't bother getting the rapier? Absolutely not. Some don't agree, but I enjoyed Rogue Redemption very much and I continue to wield my Burning Rapier with pride. I think I've seen only one other rogue with a BR in my entire EQ life. That's a better feeling than knowing there's only a fistfull of other dorf rogues out there. <br><br>P.S. Backy, you actually don't need the Rapier for the epic quest. Originally, you did; but for reasons unknown to me, Verant decided to take the easiest epic at the time and make it even easier. Check out Allakhazam's links for rogues; there's a great epic quest guide listed there with all the info and history you'd ever want to know about the RageBringer.<br><br>I haven't witnessed it for myself, but I'm pretty sure the proc on the Burning Rapier is 37dd (one more level til it starts proccing, woot!) And don't forget about that 5 Dex, 5 Agi combo.<br>&nbsp;<br>Daviv McD (Un-retired!)<br>36th Dwarf Rogue<br>Fury Fighters<br>Xegony<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13233" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13233</a></td></tr>
